2.0 release of ``The Macro Implementation of SNOBOL4 in C'' (CSNOBOL4)

	For users of earlier releases:

	A change in the "major version" number to 2.0 was chosen to
	reflect not only a major change in functionality -- addition
	of the long (thought) lost "BLOCKS" extension, and many new
	extensions (see the CHANGES file for more details), but to
	also reflect that this release DEPENDS on loadable module
	support that has only been tested on a few popular platforms
	(OS X, FreeBSD, Linux, Windows).

	The online "man pages" have been GREATLY improved.

This is a free port of the original SIL (SNOBOL4 Implementation
Language) "macro" version of SNOBOL4 (developed at Bell Labs) with the
`C' language as a target.

SNOBOL4, while known primarily as a string language excels at any task
involving symbolic manipulations.  It provides dynamic typing, garbage
collection, user data types, on the fly compilation.

The latest release can always be found at http://www.snobol4.org/csnobol4

